com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body

Class ID3v24FrameBodyUniqueFileIdentifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.beaglebuddy.util.Utility
      • com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body.ID3v24FrameBodyUtility
        • com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body.ID3v24FrameBody
          • com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body.ID3v24FrameBodyUniqueFileIdentifier

  • public class ID3v24FrameBodyUniqueFileIdentifier
extends ID3v24FrameBody

    A unique file identifier frame body is associated with an ID3v2.4 UFID frame which is used to identify the audio file in a database that may contain more information relevant to the content, such as CDDB. This is very similar to the music CD identifier frame. The ownerId URL should not be used for the actual database queries. The string "http://www.id3.org/dummy/ufid.html" should be used for tests. Software that isn't told otherwise may safely remove such frames. The unique file identifier frame body contains the following fields:

    Unique File Identifier Frame Body Fields
     FieldDescription
    1. ownerIdURL containing an e-mail address, or a link to a location where an e-mail address can be found, that belongs to the organization responsible for this specific database implementation. Questions regarding the database should be sent to the e-mail address specified.
    2. data the actual identifier, which may be up to 64 bytes.

    There may be more than one unique file identifier frame in an ID3v2.4 tag, but only one with the same owner id field.

    See Also:
    ID3v24Frame, ID3 tag version 2.4.0 standard, wikipedia history of ID3 tags
